title: The Exchange: Indonesia’s startup boom
description:
Southeast Asia's largest economy has seen a flurry of homegrown tech successes, led by $5 billion ride-hailing firm Go-Jek. Willson Cuaca of East Ventures and Donald Wihardja of Convergence Ventures explain why, and how, Jakarta can keep the hits coming. See acast.com/privacy for privacy and opt-out information.
